{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> περίφρων</b>, ονος, ὁ, ἡ, <br /> <i>vocative</i> περίφρον [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 16.435, etc., but= _nominative_, 19.357, 21.381 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: (φρήν):—<b>very thoughtful, very careful</b>, frequently in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” of Penelope, 16.435, +others; of other women, 11.345, 19.357, once in 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad”, 5.412, 3rd c.BC: Theocritus Poeta Bucolicus 3.45 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; also of Hephaestus, first in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Scutum Herculis” 297, 313; τέκνα [prev. author] “Th.” 894 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <b>artful, crafty</b>, θήρη [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd-3rd c.AD: Oppianus Anazarbensis Epicus “Halieutica - Poetae Bucolici et Didactici” 3.205. \">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>haughty, overweening</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Supplices” 757 (Lyric poetry); περίφρονα δ᾽ ἔλακες [prev. author] “Ag.” 1426 (Lyric poetry). \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__II.2</b></Level3> with <i>genitive</i>, <b>despising</b>, τῶν παθῶν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" LXX.4Mac.8.28. \">LXX</a>]","strongNumber":"G20960","accentedUnicode":"περίφρων","shortDef":"despising","mediumDef":"despising","stepGloss":"despising","stepTransliteration":"perifrōn","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}